    "Canonical Gemma Scope 2B SAEs target the same L0 per layer regardless of width (L0~72 at layers 5, ~65 at layer 12, ~68 at layer 19). This means partial rho(width | L0) is unstable: L0 varies only across layers, not within the same layer at different widths. The H6 sign-reversal test formally requires multiple L0 settings per width (extended Gemma Scope suite, not included here).",
